honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class TCPIPStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.TCPIPStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TCPIPStatus
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {TC?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    802.11B InfoWireless Card Info
    CValid Certificate Present
    CRWhen enabled this will cause the printer to report when the TCP connection is ready, or the number of connections ahead of them.
    DAcquire IP Settings
    DRIs the 802.11 radio disabled.
    EESSID
    ETEAP Type
    GPrinters Gateway Address
    IPrinters IP Address
    I2Inactivity Timeout
    LUUser Name
    LHPassword
    LU2Pass Phrase
    KKey To Use
    K1Key1
    K2Key2
    K3Key3
    K4Key4
    MPrinters Subnet Mask
    MACMAC Address
    MXMigration Mode Enabled
    NStation Name
    NANetwork Authentication
    PTCP Printing Port
    P2Power Saving Mode
    P2MPhase 2 Method
    P3UDP Printing Port
    PWRCard Powered
    QSignal Quality Indicator
    SAuthentication Algorithm
    TStation Type
    WEncryption Enabled
    ZCurrent Certificate CRC
    DNS1DNS1 Address
    RDNSRegister to DNS
    DNS2DNS2 Address
    SDNSStatic DNS
    GCGroup Cipher
    RTRadio Type
    UDNSUse DNS
    DSUFDNS Suffix
    KSEncryption Key Size
    KTEncryption Key Type

    • Constructor Detail

      • TCPIPStatus

        public TCPIPStatus(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

        public boolean getWirelessCardInfo_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getWirelessCardInfo() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getWirelessCardInfo() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
